8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both CodeGPT and Devin share a solid foundation of core features including Code Generation, Debugging, Multi Language, Chat. Where CodeGPT pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Autocomplete and Ide Integration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Devin uniquely offers Code Review and Refactoring and Test Generation and Documentation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, CodeGPT holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Devin scores 7/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, CodeGPT offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $9.99/mo, compared to Devin's starting price of $500/mo. CodeGPT has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Devin does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
