c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. CodeGPT is best suited for developers wanting LLM flexibility, VS Code users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Devin, meanwhile, shines for teams wanting autonomous coding agents, complex multi step tasks, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, CodeGPT describes itself as \"Connect any AI model to your code editor.\" Devin, established in 2023, positions itself as \"The first fully autonomous AI software engineer.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Devin** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (8 vs 6). However, this does not mean CodeGPT is a poor choice — far from it. CodeGPT excels in its own right, particularly for developers wanting LLM flexibility and VS Code users.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value can work autonomously on tasks, go with Devin. If multiple llm provider support matters more to you, CodeGPT is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
